Research has shown the number of new HIV infections has declined countrywide. CAPE TOWN – An analyst has called on the national Health Department to increase HIV/Aids education and awareness campaigns. Research has shown the number of new HIV infections has declined countrywide. The infection rate went down by 39%. The research was done by the South African Institute of Race Relations. Analyst Tawanda Makombo says more needs to be done raise awareness about HIV/Aids. “We are saying that the national Department of Health must intensify HIV/Aids awareness campaigns. Civil society must also be more involved in education and support programmes.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)